5:T4b8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"SoftwareApplication","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#app","name":"XRNotify","description":"Real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger.","url":"https://www.xrnotify.io","applicationCategory":"DeveloperApplication","operatingSystem":"Web","offers":[{"@type":"Offer","name":"Free","price":"0","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"1,000 events/month, 2 webhooks"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Starter","price":"29.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"50,000 events/month, 10 webhooks, WebSocket access"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Pro","price":"99.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"500,000 events/month, 50 webhooks, priority delivery"}],"creator":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/ali-morgan#person"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"featureList":["Real-time XRPL event ingestion","HMAC-SHA256 signed webhook delivery","Automatic retries with exponential backoff","Dead-letter queue for failed deliveries","Event replay and reprocessing","23+ XRPL event types supported","Developer dashboard with delivery logs","Per-webhook filtering by event type and account"]}6:Tcff,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#faqpage","name":"XRNotify FAQ — Common Questions About XRPL Webhooks","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify is a real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger. It monitors XRPL transactions as they confirm on-chain, normalizes them into clean JSON schemas, and delivers them to your endpoints via HMAC-signed HTTPS POST requests. XRNotify eliminates the need to run your own XRPL node or build polling infrastructure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What XRPL events does XRNotify support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify supports 23+ event types across all major XRPL transaction categories: payments (XRP and issued tokens), NFT operations (minting, burning, offers, transfers), DEX trades (OfferCreate, OfferCancel, AMM operations), trustline changes (TrustSet), escrow events (create, finish, cancel), check operations, and account-level changes like settings modifications and deletions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does webhook delivery work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When an XRPL transaction matches your configured filters, XRNotify normalizes the event, signs the payload with your webhook secret using HMAC-SHA256, and delivers it as an HTTPS POST to your endpoint. If delivery fails, XRNotify retries with exponential backoff (up to 10 attempts over 12 hours). Events that exhaust all retries are moved to a dead-letter queue for manual inspection and replay."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify offers a free tier with 1,000 events per month and 2 webhook endpoints — enough for testing and hobby projects. Paid plans start at $29/month (Starter: 50,000 events, 10 webhooks, WebSocket streaming) and $99/month (Pro: 500,000 events, 50 webhooks, priority delivery). Enterprise plans with custom SLAs are available on request."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I verify webhook signatures?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every XRNotify webhook includes an X-XRNotify-Signature header containing an HMAC-SHA256 hash of the request body, computed using your webhook signing secret. To verify, compute the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw request body with your secret and compare it to the header value using a constant-time comparison function to prevent timing attacks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who built XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify was built by Ali Morgan, founder of Jonomor, a systems architecture studio focused on AI Visibility and real-time infrastructure intelligence. XRNotify is the XRPL instrumentation layer of the Jonomor ecosystem, which also includes Guard-Clause, MyPropOps, The Neutral Bridge, Evenfield, and H.U.N.I.E."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. XRNotify is part of the Jonomor ecosystem, a suite of interconnected software products built by Ali Morgan. Within the ecosystem, XRNotify serves as the real-time observation layer — detecting XRPL events at the point of origin before they flow through interpretation and operational layers in other Jonomor properties."}}]}0:["pQjrRFT3j-NbWRfetFzsE",[[["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","main",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0f]","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"border-b border-white/5 px-6 py-5 lg:px-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-6xl flex items-center justify-between","children":["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard","className":"text-sm text-zinc-400 no-underline transition-colors hover:text-white","children":"← Back to Dashboard"}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"border-b border-white/5 py-20","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl","children":"Documentation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-zinc-400","children":"Everything you need to integrate XRNotify into your application. From quick starts to API reference."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs/quickstart","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-white bg-blue-600 border border-blue-500 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-blue-700 hover:shadow-lg transition-all focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-[#0a0a0f]","children":["Quick Start Gui